t\naccessible to you during execution.\n\n## Your goal\n\nYou are given `input/counts.tsv` (gene \u00d7 sample) and `input/metadata.tsv`\n(first column sample_name, plus a `treatment` column with `UT`/`TR`). Run the\nepigen `dea_limma` pipeline (design=`~treatment`, TMM + voom + eBayes) and write:\n  - `output/dea_results.csv` with columns `feature, logFC, AveExpr, t, P.Value,\n    adj.P.Val, B, group` (fwrite).\n  - `output/lmfit.rds` (fitted limma `lmFit` object, via `saveRDS`).\n  - `output/model_matrix.csv` (fwrite with row.names=TRUE).\nDo not persist any image output.\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- At least `output/dea_results.csv` must exist when you submit.\n- Full output set expected: dea_results.csv, model_matrix.csv under `output/`.\n\nWhen the deliverables are in `output/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n\n## Workspace (read-only summary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"counts.tsv\": {\n      \"_file\": \"counts.tsv\"\n    },\n    \"metadata.tsv\": {\n      \"_file\": \"metadata.tsv\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/dea_results.csv` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_oNI54NYwmgNXAYCTuVuB2hwc", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Load the necessary libraries for differential expression analysis using limma.\\n2. Read the input data files: `counts.tsv` for gene expression data and `metadata.tsv` for sample metadata.\\n3. Prepare the design matrix using the formula `~treatment`.\\n4. Normalize the data using TMM normalization with `edgeR::calcNormFactors`.\\n5. Apply the `voom` transformation to model the mean-variance relationship.\\n6. Fit the linear model using `lmFit` and apply empirical Bayes moderation wi